1.caption_en:
Based on a survey of 150+ platform executives, most platforms lack key IT capabilities that slow market traction and scalability; top issues reported are limited interoperability (88%), inability to extract meaningful data insights (85%), inefficient interactions (75%), and inability to scale (73%).

{
  "title": "Most platforms lack key IT capabilities which slows down market traction and scalability",
  "source": "Survey of 150+ platform executives, fastbreak.one, 2021",
  "sample_size": 150,
  "year": 2021,
  "visualization_type": "four circular percentage indicators",
  "issues": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Limited interoperability",
      "percent": 88,
      "description": "Inefficient processes between ecosystem players that reduce the platform's core value proposition to users."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "name": "Inability to draw meaningful insights out of data",
      "percent": 85,
      "description": "Driven by inability to collect data and low capabilities to analyze insights and use artificial intelligence on major data sets."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "name": "Inefficient interactions",
      "percent": 75,
      "description": "Low velocity and liquidity of interactions between platform stakeholders, limiting the ability to monetize platforms."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "name": "Inability to scale",
      "percent": 73,
      "description": "Often caused by a highly complex IT infrastructure composed of different systems and components."
    }
  ]
}

